## PWA (Mobile)

You can install Breader as a Progressive Web App on your mobile device:

1. Open Breader in your mobile browser
2. Look for the "Install" or "Add to Home Screen" option in your browser menu
3. Follow the prompts to install

Once installed, you can share links from any mobile app directly to Breader using your phone's share menu.

## Organizing Bookmarks

**Tags**: Click on a bookmark to add tags or drag and drop it on a tag. Tags help you organize your bookmarks into categories.

**Tag Hierarchy**: Drag and drop a tag onto another tag to create nested structures (like folders within folders).

**Multiple Tags**: Each bookmark can have multiple tags and will appear under all of them.

## Reading Statuses

Each bookmark can have one of four statuses:

- **Want to Read**: Bookmarks you plan to read later (default for new bookmarks)
- **Reading**: Bookmarks you're currently reading
- **Read**: Bookmarks you've finished reading
- **Archived**: Bookmarks you want to keep but remove from active lists

Click on a bookmark to change its status.

## Search

Press <kbd class="kbd">Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd class="kbd">K</kbd> (or <kbd class="kbd">Cmd</kbd> + <kbd class="kbd">K</kbd> on Mac) to focus the search bar.

The search finds bookmarks by title, tags, and keywords using fuzzy matching - so you don't need to type the exact words.

## Notes

You can attach notes to any bookmark to save your thoughts, key insights, or context:

1. Click on a bookmark to open its details
2. Find the notes section
3. Add or edit your notes
4. Notes are saved automatically

A single note can be attached to multiple bookmarks.

## Starring

Click the star icon on any bookmark to mark it as a favorite.

Starred bookmarks can be quickly filtered in your library for easy access to your most important items.
